cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a novel approach to train deep CNNs for image classification, which is a common task in computer vision (CV) research. The approach focuses on enhancing the discriminant power of learned features, which is a key aspect of machine learning (ML) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces new loss functions and optimization methods, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (MM) research. Therefore, cs.MM is also a likely sub-category.
